\section{Structural Relationships}

\begin{itemize}[leftmargin=*]
    \item Law of total probability $\rightarrow$ Bayes’ theorem
    \item Conditional probability $\rightarrow$ Posterior probability
    \item Sample space $\rightarrow$ Random variable $\rightarrow$ PMF
    \item Discrete random variable $\rightarrow$ Probability mass function
\end{itemize}

\section{Consolidated Summary}

\begin{itemize}[leftmargin=*]
    \item Probability of an event can be expressed as a weighted average of conditional probabilities.
    \item Bayes’ theorem updates prior probabilities using observed evidence.
    \item Random variables map experimental outcomes to numerical values.
    \item Discrete random variables are described using PMFs.
    \item PMFs satisfy non-negativity and total probability equal to 1.
\end{itemize}

